This is great. We now have a dashboard that tracks all the hyperparameters, metrics, artifacts for all the models we have trained with no extra efforts. However, notice that this server is hosted and being used on localhost:5000 i.e. your own computer. What if you are working in a team and want to collaborate with other members to work on the same project or even just read the information from the dashboard. This will not be possible unless you setup a remote server.

For this example, the app has been hosted on streamlit.io. Here is the link to the app.

The application can also be run locally using the Anaconda Prompt by moving to the folder where app.py lives and typing streamlit run app.py.
